    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "A regular spa massage table is often padded and designed for general bodywork, while an Ayurveda massage table is typically wooden, oil-resistant, and built with features like drainage systems for oil-heavy treatments. It supports therapies like Shirodhara, Abhyanga, and Pizhichil, where traditional design enhances the therapy’s authenticity and effectiveness."
    }
  },{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "Why is drainage important in a Shirodhara massage bed?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "Shirodhara involves a continuous stream of oil being poured on the forehead. A shirodhara massage bed must have an efficient drainage system to collect and remove excess oil. This not only maintains hygiene and reusability but also ensures a mess-free experience for both the client and therapist, preserving the aesthetics of your treatment room."
    }
  },{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "Can I use a Shirodhara table for other types of massage?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "Yes. A shirodhara table is versatile and can be used for other oil-based Ayurvedic treatments such as Abhyanga, Pizhichil, and Udvartana. However, its design may not be as comfortable as a padded spa massage table for dry massages or modern Western treatments unless upgraded with cushions or bolsters."
    }
  },{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "What material is best for an Ayurveda massage table?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "Traditionally, Ayurveda massage tables are made from teak, rosewood, or neem wood for their durability and natural antimicrobial properties. However, modern options now include waterproof coatings, reinforced wooden bases, or steel for structural support. At Spa Furniture, we offer wooden options enhanced with oil-resistant coatings for longevity."
    }
  },{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "How do I maintain my spa massage table after oil treatments?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "Proper maintenance involves wiping down the surface after each use with mild soap and warm water, especially after heavy oil use. For wooden shirodhara tables, avoid harsh cleaners that damage the finish. Regular polishing, checking the drainage system, and using disposable sheets or towels can prolong the life of your spa massage table."
    }
  }]
}
